<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-71-0349 </DOCNO><TEXT>The U.S. Nuclear Regulatory Commission is responsible for the regulationof the commercial uses of nuclear power in the United States in orderto protect the public health and safety. The NRC has undertaken a numberof initiatives to incorporate the experience gained from the over 25years of commercial nuclear power plant operation. These initiativesare aimed at improving the regulatory structure currently in place byproviding for a more predictable and stable regulatory environment andby more efficiently and effectively focusing the activities of utilitieson the safe operation of their facilities.</TEXT></DOC>